    Take Life on the Go with a Laptop

    For life on the go, a laptop can keep up with your demands wherever you are. With the functionality of a desktop computer packed into a portable device, a laptop lets you connect to the web, watch movies, play games, edit photos and so much more. Whether you‚Äôre looking for a standard laptop, 2 in 1 laptop or MacBook, Best Buy has a wide selection from ASUS, Microsoft, Samsung, HP , Toshiba and Apple to suit your needs.

    Processors

    The processor is the brain of the laptop, interpreting and performing all its commands. Intel and AMD both make processors that are tailor-made for different needs‚Äîfrom basic tasks like sending emails to demanding ones like simultaneously running multiple applications. To ensure you‚Äôve got the right processor for your needs, consider individual specs like number of cores, overclock ability and speed.

    Screen Size and Resolution

    Size matters when it comes to laptops. A larger screen will likely make the device heavier but will give you plenty of room to work and play. A smaller screen size will make it lighter and more compact, perfect for taking on the go. Most laptops have a screen resolution of at least Full HD (1920 x 1080), and there are many options even higher resolution, even 4K!

    Family Friendly Laptops

    Many people are looking for a versatile and dependable machine that is great for the whole family. There are many great options available that offer great processing power, amazing screen resolution and responsiveness and are designed to handle a wide variety of purposes. For example, Microsoft Surface family includes the tablet style Surface Pro, the Surface Laptop and the Surface Book‚Äîthere is machine to suit anyone‚Äôs needs. For people more familiar with Apple computers , there are a variety of configurations, including the MacBook , MacBook Pro and MacBook Air , to ensure no matter how demanding the job, you‚Äôll be able to complete it on your MacBook. Your children will excel with any of these computer: Microsoft and Apple manufacture some of the best laptops for students.

    2 in 1 and Hybrid Laptops

    A 2 in 1 laptop (also called convertible or hybrid laptop) combines the functionality of a laptop with the convenience of a tablet . Equipped with both a touchscreen and a keyboard, a 2 in 1 laptop can transform from laptop to tablet in various ways‚Äîby folding back, rotating or detaching the screen, depending on the model. A 2 in 1 is perfect when you want both a laptop and a tablet without having to buy two separate devices. If you are looking for a versatile machine, consider a Surface Pro, a Surface Laptop or a MacBook.

    Why should I upgrade or get a premium laptop?

    A premium laptop will support you in being as productive as possible, both at the office and at home. This is especially useful if you are engaging in a hybrid work schedule or doing schoolwork from the comfort of your humble abode. Premium laptops and premium gaming laptops offer greater processing power to handle more intensive tasks as well as multitasking. They have gorgeous screens, and better battery life to last through a full work or school day. Switching from work to entertainment is a breeze, whether you‚Äôre gaming, streaming videos, or doing other activities. With a better screen, more storage and RAM, along with an improved graphics card, the computer will be able to keep up with your demanding needs, no matter where you are nor what you‚Äôre doing.

    Save money with our outlet deals

    On a tight budget? You don‚Äôt have to sacrifice on features and processing power. You can find great deals on open box and refurbished laptops from our outlet. Laptops that are Geek Squad Certified Open Box undergo stringent testing by our team of experts to ensure that they meet performance standards and work like new. Going with an open box or refurbished laptop is a great way to scale up to a model and/or specs that you need (or to future-proof the investment) while saving money in the process.
